PRETORIA - The Absa Premiership match between Mamelodi Sundowns and Chippa United at Loftus was abandoned on Tuesday night.With the score goalless after 41 minutes, the floodlights went out because of a power failure.The power failure affected Loftus and the surrounding areas. The information relayed to officials was that it would take more than two hours to fix the problem.The delayed fixture will resume at 10am at Loftus Stadium on Wednesday.If you purchased a ticket yesterday, you will be allowed entry using that ticket. #SundownsAfrican News Agency